---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Breathe Easy - Support"
  description="Get help with Breathe Easy - Guided Breathing Timer iOS app."
  ogUrl="https://idlefusion.com/breathe-easy/support"
>
  <main>
    <section class="section-padding">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-8">Support</h1>

        <div class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-12">
          <p class="text-lg mb-4">Need help with Breathe Easy?</p>
          <p>Check out the frequently asked questions below, or send us an email at <a href="mailto:matthew@idlefusion.com?subject=Breathe%20Easy%20Support%20Request" class="text-[var(--accent-primary)] hover:underline">matthew@idlefusion.com</a> and we'll get back to you as soon as we can.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">What breathing patterns are available?</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">Breathe Easy includes three proven breathing patterns: Box Breathing (4-4-4-4), 4-7-8 Relaxation, and Coherent Breathing (5-5). Each is designed to help you relax, focus, or prepare for sleep.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">How do I use the Apple Watch app?</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">The Apple Watch app runs completely standalone — no iPhone required. Open the app on your watch, select a breathing pattern, and start. Haptic cues guide you through each inhale, hold, and exhale phase.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">How does HealthKit integration work?</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">When you grant permission, Breathe Easy saves completed sessions to Apple Health as mindfulness minutes. This is optional — the app works fully without it. You can enable or disable this in Settings at any time.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">Can I customize session duration?</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">Yes! In Settings, you can adjust the default duration for each breathing pattern. Sessions can be as short as 1 minute or as long as you like.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">How do I use the widgets?</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">Long-press on your Home Screen or Lock Screen and tap the "+" button to add widgets. Breathe Easy offers small and medium Home Screen widgets, plus circular and rectangular Lock Screen widgets for quick session access.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">Is my data private?</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">Absolutely. Breathe Easy collects zero data. There are no analytics, no tracking, and no network requests. Your session history stays on your device. Read our <a href="/breathe-easy/privacy" class="text-[var(--accent-primary)] hover:underline">privacy policy</a> for full details.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">The app isn't syncing between my iPhone and Apple Watch</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">Breathe Easy stores session data locally on each device. If you have HealthKit enabled on both devices, your mindfulness minutes will appear in Apple Health regardless of which device you used.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-[var(--border-primary)]">
          <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)]">
            Still have questions? Email us at <a href="mailto:matthew@idlefusion.com?subject=Breathe%20Easy%20Support%20Request" class="text-[var(--accent-primary)] hover:underline">matthew@idlefusion.com</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
